<doc id="1135500" wikidata="Q2411585" url="?curid=1135500" title="Gibson Steps">
<text>The Gibson Steps are an area of cliffs on the south coast of Australia, located at . The cliffs are the first sightseeing stopoff in Port Campbell National Park for travellers heading West along the Great Ocean Road, located about 2 minutes drive from The Twelve Apostles. The name Gibson Steps refers to the staircase leading down to Gibson Beach.

